Below is a **complete, practical list of Oracle DATE & DATE-TIME functions**, grouped by category.
(This covers what you‚Äôll actually use in real projects üëç)

---

# üóìÔ∏è Oracle DATE & DATE-TIME Functions

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ Current Date / Time Functions

| Function            | Description                            |
| ------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| `SYSDATE`           | Current date & time (server timezone)  |
| `CURRENT_DATE`      | Current date & time (session timezone) |
| `SYSTIMESTAMP`      | Timestamp with time zone               |
| `CURRENT_TIMESTAMP` | Timestamp in session timezone          |
| `LOCALTIMESTAMP`    | Timestamp without time zone            |
| `DBTIMEZONE`        | Database time zone                     |
| `SESSIONTIMEZONE`   | Session time zone                      |

```sql
SELECT SYSDATE, SYSTIMESTAMP FROM dual;
```

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£ Date Arithmetic (Add / Subtract)

| Function                 | Description          |
| ------------------------ | -------------------- |
| `+ / -`                  | Add or subtract days |
| `ADD_MONTHS(date, n)`    | Add months           |
| `MONTHS_BETWEEN(d1, d2)` | Difference in months |
| `NEXT_DAY(date, 'DAY')`  | Next weekday         |
| `LAST_DAY(date)`         | Last day of month    |

```sql
SELECT SYSDATE + 7, ADD_MONTHS(SYSDATE, 1) FROM dual;
```

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£ Date Difference (Days / Time)

| Method                        | Result               |
| ----------------------------- | -------------------- |
| `date2 - date1`               | Days (with fraction) |
| `TRUNC(date2) - TRUNC(date1)` | Whole days           |

```sql
SELECT end_date - start_date FROM dual;
```

---

## 4Ô∏è‚É£ Date Formatting (DATE ‚Üí STRING)

| Function                | Description            |
| ----------------------- | ---------------------- |
| `TO_CHAR(date, format)` | Convert date to string |

```sql
SELECT TO_CHAR(SYSDATE, 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS') FROM dual;
```

---

## 5Ô∏è‚É£ String ‚Üí Date / Timestamp

| Function                        | Description                |
| ------------------------------- | -------------------------- |
| `TO_DATE(char, format)`         | String ‚Üí DATE              |
| `TO_TIMESTAMP(char, format)`    | String ‚Üí TIMESTAMP         |
| `TO_TIMESTAMP_TZ(char, format)` | String ‚Üí TIMESTAMP WITH TZ |

```sql
SELECT TO_DATE('2026-01-08', 'YYYY-MM-DD') FROM dual;
```

---

## 6Ô∏è‚É£ Date Truncation & Rounding

| Function             | Description          |
| -------------------- | -------------------- |
| `TRUNC(date, 'fmt')` | Remove smaller units |
| `ROUND(date, 'fmt')` | Round date           |

```sql
SELECT TRUNC(SYSDATE, 'MM'), ROUND(SYSDATE, 'YYYY') FROM dual;
```

---

## 7Ô∏è‚É£ Extract Parts of Date

| Function                   | Description    |
| -------------------------- | -------------- |
| `EXTRACT(YEAR FROM date)`  | Extract year   |
| `EXTRACT(MONTH FROM date)` | Extract month  |
| `EXTRACT(DAY FROM date)`   | Extract day    |
| `EXTRACT(HOUR FROM ts)`    | Extract hour   |
| `EXTRACT(MINUTE FROM ts)`  | Extract minute |
| `EXTRACT(SECOND FROM ts)`  | Extract second |

```sql
SELECT EXTRACT(YEAR FROM SYSDATE) FROM dual;
```

---

## 8Ô∏è‚É£ Time Zone Functions

| Function                | Description         |
| ----------------------- | ------------------- |
| `FROM_TZ(ts, tz)`       | Add TZ to timestamp |
| `CAST(ts AS TIMESTAMP)` | Convert type        |
| `AT TIME ZONE`          | Convert timezone    |
| `SYS_EXTRACT_UTC(ts)`   | Convert to UTC      |

```sql
SELECT SYSTIMESTAMP AT TIME ZONE 'UTC' FROM dual;
```

---

## 9Ô∏è‚É£ ISO / Week-Based Functions

| Function                  | Description       |
| ------------------------- | ----------------- |
| `TRUNC(date, 'IW')`       | Start of ISO week |
| `TO_CHAR(date, 'IW')`     | ISO week number   |
| `TO_CHAR(date, 'YYYYIW')` | ISO year + week   |

---

## üîü Validation & Comparison Helpers

| Function                 | Description         |
| ------------------------ | ------------------- |
| `NVL(date, SYSDATE)`     | Handle NULL dates   |
| `COALESCE(date1, date2)` | First non-null date |
| `GREATEST(d1, d2)`       | Latest date         |
| `LEAST(d1, d2)`          | Earliest date       |

---

## üö´ Functions Oracle Does NOT Have

(From MySQL / SQL Server)

| Function      | Status          |
| ------------- | --------------- |
| `DATEDIFF`    | ‚ùå Not in Oracle |
| `DATE_FORMAT` | ‚ùå Not in Oracle |
| `GETDATE()`   | ‚ùå Use `SYSDATE` |

---

## ‚≠ê Most Used in Real Projects

‚úî `SYSDATE`
‚úî `ADD_MONTHS`
‚úî `LAST_DAY`
‚úî `TO_CHAR` / `TO_DATE`
‚úî `TRUNC(date)`
‚úî `EXTRACT`

---

## üìå Best Practice (Important)

‚ùå Don‚Äôt rely on `NLS_DATE_FORMAT`
‚úÖ Always use explicit formats:

```sql
TO_DATE('2026-01-08', 'YYYY-MM-DD')
```

